WEBVTT

00:02.127 --> 00:04.421
Places, everyone.
It's show time!

00:04.421 --> 00:06.298
Can we please not do this?

00:06.298 --> 00:08.008
Ray, it's a new neighborhood.

00:08.008 --> 00:09.510
We've got to find out
which is fastest.

00:09.510 --> 00:10.511
It's unnecessary.

00:10.511 --> 00:11.637
‐3... 2..
‐It's probably illegal.

00:11.637 --> 00:12.930
[ Buttons beep ]

00:15.098 --> 00:16.225
[ Sighs ]

00:16.225 --> 00:17.559
Are we ever
gonna get our furniture

00:17.559 --> 00:18.602
from the old house?

00:18.602 --> 00:20.437
There's no place
for anyone to sit.

00:23.649 --> 00:25.692
Uh, he's right. Up.
You've hogged it long enough.

00:25.692 --> 00:26.985
[ Chuckles ]

00:26.985 --> 00:28.028
[ Sirens approaching ]
Ooh.

00:28.028 --> 00:29.071
Health Alert
or Medic‐Call?

00:29.071 --> 00:30.447
[ Tires screech ]
Who's the winner?

00:30.447 --> 00:31.865
Someone pressed
a Health Alert pendant?

00:31.865 --> 00:33.283
Sorry.
It was a false alarm.

00:33.283 --> 00:34.910
But we do have
a special‐needs child

00:34.910 --> 00:36.245
who at some point
in the future

00:36.245 --> 00:38.038
may require
immediate medical care.

00:38.038 --> 00:40.040
Your response time
was exceptional.

00:40.040 --> 00:41.416
Please accept
this basket

00:41.416 --> 00:43.377
as a token
of our deepest gratitude

00:43.377 --> 00:45.420
for your time
and your service.

00:46.755 --> 00:48.507
Too late.
He died.

00:48.507 --> 00:50.050
♪♪

00:57.140 --> 00:59.726
Listen, whoever you
want to be your aide,
I'll make it happen.

00:59.726 --> 01:00.894
I mean,
that's what I do.

01:00.894 --> 01:02.854
But why this gardener man?

01:02.854 --> 01:05.148
I mean, what makes you think
that he's the one for the job?

01:05.148 --> 01:07.859
"I like him."

01:07.859 --> 01:09.027
Yeah, what else?

01:09.027 --> 01:10.612
"You don't."

01:10.612 --> 01:12.072
[ Scoffs ] JJ.

01:12.072 --> 01:13.824
He mows grass
for a living.

01:13.824 --> 01:16.868
This is a man whose chief
job competition is goats.

01:16.868 --> 01:19.997
Um, Mrs. DiMeo,
I‐I‐I'm right here.

01:19.997 --> 01:22.124
Aww. You thought
that would embarrass her.

01:22.124 --> 01:23.292
That's cute.

01:23.292 --> 01:26.962
Look, we got off
on the wrong foot.

01:26.962 --> 01:28.589
I'd like
to give you something.

01:29.881 --> 01:32.259
Hee‐hee! Yeah.

01:32.259 --> 01:33.260
She's smiling, right?

01:35.596 --> 01:37.389
That's right.

01:37.389 --> 01:39.558
So, I, uh,
I'm excited.

01:39.558 --> 01:40.601
Little nervous.

01:40.601 --> 01:42.185
You're gonna
have to help me out.

01:42.185 --> 01:45.022
I've never been an aide
before.

01:45.022 --> 01:46.565
"I've never had one."

01:46.565 --> 01:48.066
Oh.

01:48.066 --> 01:50.193
Okay, well, this isn't
gonna work out at all.

01:50.193 --> 01:51.528
[ Both chuckle ]

01:52.487 --> 01:54.698
"Have questions?"

01:54.698 --> 01:56.241
I‐I do, actually.

01:56.241 --> 01:59.703
What perspective does the
disability experience lend ‐‐

01:59.703 --> 02:01.955
"Real questions."

02:01.955 --> 02:04.458
[ Claps hands ]
Okay, let's do this.

02:04.458 --> 02:06.543
Do I handle
bathroom stuff?

02:06.543 --> 02:07.836
Does your dude‐stuff work?

02:07.836 --> 02:09.504
Is my voice good
to speak for you?

02:09.504 --> 02:11.131
[ Deep voice ]
I can go lower.

02:11.131 --> 02:12.883
[ Normal voice ]
Are you like Rain Man?
Do you count cards?

02:12.883 --> 02:14.134
Should we go to Vegas?

02:14.134 --> 02:16.428
Okay, you're a liar.
That's good to know.

02:16.428 --> 02:18.513
So, how can I help
the DiMeos?

02:18.513 --> 02:20.432
You're conflicted.
Let me sell this.

02:23.018 --> 02:24.144
Well,
we have a request.

02:24.144 --> 02:25.479
Don't ask.
Tell. Firm.

02:25.479 --> 02:27.439
Fine.
What we want ‐‐
Need.

02:27.439 --> 02:29.274
What we need ‐‐ and we realize
this is unconventional,

02:29.274 --> 02:30.442
but ‐‐
Oh, love.

02:30.442 --> 02:32.152
We have dismissed
our son's aide

02:32.152 --> 02:33.403
and chosen
his replacement.

02:33.403 --> 02:35.572
It's your groundskeeper.
He starts tomorrow.

02:35.572 --> 02:36.865
Yeah.

02:36.865 --> 02:38.367
Kenneth!
That's wonderful!

02:38.367 --> 02:40.577
He's a natural‐born
caregiver.

02:40.577 --> 02:42.788
And he's already part
of the Lafayette High family.

02:42.788 --> 02:43.789
I support it
wholeheartedly.

02:44.915 --> 02:46.708
Does no one understand
how these things go?

02:46.708 --> 02:49.336
You don't just say "Yes."
You push back.

02:49.336 --> 02:51.171
That way,
we owe you something.

02:51.171 --> 02:53.423
Okay, watch
for next time.
Yes.

02:53.423 --> 02:55.008
"We're hiring
the gardener."

02:55.008 --> 02:56.551
"As an aide?
Preposterous!"

02:56.551 --> 02:58.220
"It's our decision.
It's our son."

02:58.220 --> 02:59.554
"It's my school!"

02:59.554 --> 03:01.181
"Well, it won't be when
our lawyers are done with you."

03:01.181 --> 03:04.393
[ Gasps ]
"So you're going to sue me now?

03:04.393 --> 03:07.187
Fine! I approve it
on a trial basis.

03:07.187 --> 03:09.314
But do not mistake my kindness
for weakness.

03:09.314 --> 03:10.774
I will not be threatened,

03:10.774 --> 03:14.653
and you are not the only one
with lawyers, bitch!"

03:14.653 --> 03:18.865
"... trial... basis."

03:18.865 --> 03:20.367
This is fantastic.

03:20.367 --> 03:22.411
Hey.
What are you working on?

03:22.411 --> 03:24.663
[ Sighs ]
The girl I like, Jillian,

03:24.663 --> 03:26.957
I'm trying to find
some time to talk to her.

03:26.957 --> 03:28.708
This is the school.

03:28.708 --> 03:30.085
The green dots
are her schedule,

03:30.085 --> 03:31.962
and the red dots
are her boyfriend Zane's.

03:31.962 --> 03:35.173
It's all day.
I can't get a minute alone.

03:35.173 --> 03:36.842
Be patient.
You'll find a window.

03:36.842 --> 03:38.510
And shred this.

03:38.510 --> 03:40.345
[ Wheels rattling ]

03:40.345 --> 03:42.097
No.
Oh, no. No!

03:42.097 --> 03:44.724
Dylan.
Dylan, stop.

03:44.724 --> 03:46.601
We can't have the neighbors
seeing you cleaning up ‐‐

03:46.601 --> 03:47.686
sends a bad message.

03:47.686 --> 03:48.687
What message?

03:48.687 --> 03:49.938
That we clean up.

03:49.938 --> 03:52.232
Listen,
you're of an age ‐‐

03:52.232 --> 03:53.567
I want to say 12 ‐‐

03:53.567 --> 03:55.652
where it's time
that you learn who we are

03:55.652 --> 03:57.112
and ‐‐ and how we deal
with people.

03:57.112 --> 03:58.613
I'm so ready.
Okay.

03:58.613 --> 04:01.700
Our family has
a complicated life,

04:01.700 --> 04:03.869
so things are gonna fall
through the cracks.

04:03.869 --> 04:05.745
Lawns aren't
gonna get mowed,

04:05.745 --> 04:07.289
garbage bins
aren't gonna get taken in.

04:07.289 --> 04:09.082
It's best to be clear
about that.

04:09.082 --> 04:12.294
It's the DiMeo way.
We've set the bar nice and low.

04:12.294 --> 04:14.504
[ Door closes ]
Oh, no.
He's coming over.

04:14.504 --> 04:16.506
All right. Just keep quiet
and don't look cute.

04:18.258 --> 04:19.217
Damn it, child.
That's adorable.

04:19.217 --> 04:21.595
Well, hello, there
[Sighs] neighbor.

04:21.595 --> 04:22.721
My name's Tom.

04:22.721 --> 04:24.431
Hey. [ Sighs ]

04:24.431 --> 04:26.141
And your name is...?
[ Chuckles ]

04:27.350 --> 04:29.019
Jimmy.
My name's Jimmy.

04:29.019 --> 04:31.396
Well, I brought you
a lovely welcoming gift.

04:31.396 --> 04:33.148
They're my famous
[French accent] macarons.

04:33.148 --> 04:35.150
[ Normal voice ] I can't
tell you how wonderful it is

04:35.150 --> 04:36.485
to have a nice family
move in.

04:36.485 --> 04:39.070
The last owner,
he just really let the place go.

04:39.070 --> 04:40.822
You're, uh ‐‐

04:40.822 --> 04:42.199
She's really
eating them fast.

04:43.617 --> 04:45.535
Anyway, if you'd like,
I would gladly give you

04:45.535 --> 04:47.329
the name
of a wonderful landscaper,

04:47.329 --> 04:48.622
handyman, painter ‐‐
whatever you need.

04:48.622 --> 04:50.415
Ah, we're ‐‐ we're really more
do‐it‐yourselfers...

04:50.415 --> 04:51.583
Oh.

04:51.583 --> 04:52.584
... w‐who don't do it.

04:52.584 --> 04:54.419
I see.

04:54.419 --> 04:55.378
Okay.

04:57.839 --> 04:59.341
You know,
they're supposed to be savored.

05:01.676 --> 05:03.053
[ Clears throat ]

05:03.053 --> 05:06.598
♪♪

05:06.598 --> 05:08.934
Right, he has physical therapy
today at 4:00,

05:08.934 --> 05:10.519
and I've packed
his lunch.

05:10.519 --> 05:12.562
It's all cut up
into small pieces
to avoid choking.

05:12.562 --> 05:13.814
[ Laughs ]

05:13.814 --> 05:15.148
What's so funny?

05:15.148 --> 05:17.692
Sorry, it's just, um ‐‐
Well, you had to be there.

05:17.692 --> 05:19.694
I <i>was ‐‐</i> right here,

05:19.694 --> 05:22.239
trying to instruct you
on how not to kill my son.

05:23.740 --> 05:26.409
Everything you need to know
is in this book.

05:26.409 --> 05:28.119
The kid comes
with instructions?

05:28.119 --> 05:30.288
Feeding, communication...

05:30.288 --> 05:31.289
Culture?

05:31.289 --> 05:33.208
His favorite show
is "The Bachelor"?

05:33.208 --> 05:35.168
Yes.
It's our tradition.

05:35.168 --> 05:37.170
We have a date
every Monday night.

05:37.170 --> 05:38.588
[ Laughs ]

05:38.588 --> 05:40.465
Oh, you're serious.

05:40.465 --> 05:42.092
This is beautiful ‐‐

05:42.092 --> 05:46.012
the bond between a...
mother and... son.

05:47.222 --> 05:48.598
[ Both snicker ]

05:51.309 --> 05:52.853
[ Engine starts ]
Ooh! Wait!

05:52.853 --> 05:54.312
Hold on!

05:54.312 --> 05:57.357
Right. Here's a sweater
in case he get cold.

05:57.357 --> 06:00.110
And this is sunblock
'cause he's very fair.

06:00.110 --> 06:02.487
And if there's
a medical emergency,

06:02.487 --> 06:05.824
one of these is very fast,
and one isn't.

06:05.824 --> 06:08.159
I don't remember.
Press them both.

06:08.159 --> 06:09.828
He's gonna be okay.

06:09.828 --> 06:11.955
This is hard for me.

06:11.955 --> 06:13.582
He's my world.

06:13.582 --> 06:15.917
Look.

06:15.917 --> 06:18.795
I admit, I don't
have this figured out.

06:18.795 --> 06:20.463
It felt like a challenge

06:20.463 --> 06:22.424
and also a good way
to help somebody.

06:22.424 --> 06:25.302
I will earn your trust,
Mrs. DiMeo.

06:25.302 --> 06:27.178
Your son is in good hands.

06:33.268 --> 06:35.604
[ Tires screech ]

06:36.688 --> 06:38.064
[ Brakes screech ]

06:38.064 --> 06:40.901
I'm not gonna lie.

06:40.901 --> 06:42.068
That sucked.

06:45.155 --> 06:47.198
♪♪

06:49.034 --> 06:51.244
Jillian.
You're alone.

06:51.244 --> 06:52.912
Don't you and Zane
have Spanish together?

06:52.912 --> 06:54.331
Zane? No,
he switched to Mandarin.

06:54.331 --> 06:55.332
What's that?

06:55.332 --> 06:56.875
Uh...it's a contract.

06:56.875 --> 06:58.460
I'm leasing a car.

06:58.460 --> 06:59.961
Bad idea.
I am too young.

06:59.961 --> 07:02.005
So, Mandarin?
Like the oranges.

07:02.005 --> 07:03.590
Like 'em? I love 'em!
[ Chuckles ]

07:03.590 --> 07:05.342
You can put them on salad
or you can eat them alone.

07:05.342 --> 07:06.468
You got to peel them,
though.

07:06.468 --> 07:07.677
It's a lot of work.
It's not worth it.

07:07.677 --> 07:09.054
Uh, all right.

07:12.891 --> 07:14.934
I have a window.
Yes!

07:14.934 --> 07:15.685
[ Cellphone rings ]

07:15.685 --> 07:16.686
Mrs. DiMeo.

07:16.686 --> 07:17.771
<i>Hello, Kenneth.</i>

07:17.771 --> 07:19.105
Just checking to see

07:19.105 --> 07:20.857
you arrived safely at school
with my son

07:20.857 --> 07:23.568
and that, once there,
removed him from the van.

07:23.568 --> 07:25.737
We're in school,
and JJ's doing just fine.

07:25.737 --> 07:28.031
Here he is.
You can ask him yourself.

07:28.031 --> 07:30.241
<i>Did he just put you</i>
<i>on the phone?</i>

07:30.241 --> 07:32.577
Take the phone back,
Kenneth!

07:32.577 --> 07:34.287
<i>The boy doesn't speak!</i>

07:34.287 --> 07:36.873
That's kind of
the whole thing!

07:36.873 --> 07:38.166
Roger that.

07:38.166 --> 07:39.501
<i>Have a great day,</i>
<i>Mrs. DiMeo.</i>

07:39.501 --> 07:40.710
<i>[ Chuckles ]</i>

07:40.710 --> 07:43.296
All right, um,
let's get down to business.

07:43.296 --> 07:45.256
There's a lot
going on here.

07:45.256 --> 07:48.176
Are you a sports guy
or, uh, you into music?

07:48.176 --> 07:49.260
What do you think about?

07:54.349 --> 07:55.809
Okay.

07:57.686 --> 07:59.020
Mm‐hmm.

07:59.020 --> 08:00.397
That's curious.

08:00.397 --> 08:02.440
I didn't notice a "butt" section
in the book.

08:02.440 --> 08:04.067
Might an aide help
in that department?

08:05.276 --> 08:06.778
All right.

08:06.778 --> 08:09.406
First thing, uh, we got to do
something about <i>this.</i>

08:09.406 --> 08:10.865
Ugh.

08:10.865 --> 08:11.950
Let's go shopping.

08:11.950 --> 08:13.868
Kenneth:
Uh, lost‐and‐found, please.

08:13.868 --> 08:15.829
My friend misplaced
some things.

08:15.829 --> 08:16.830
What did he lose?

08:16.830 --> 08:18.623
Let's see what you got.

08:18.623 --> 08:20.041
Come on, JJ!

08:20.041 --> 08:21.042
♪♪

08:21.042 --> 08:23.044
It's a girl's shirt,
man.

08:23.044 --> 08:24.003
It buttons
on the wrong side.

08:24.963 --> 08:26.131
Yeah, but <i>I'll</i> know.

08:29.217 --> 08:30.719
We said we'd try.
Now we know.

08:32.303 --> 08:34.681
Yeah,
I'm liking this.

08:34.681 --> 08:35.807
Wait a second.

08:35.807 --> 08:37.642
Young man...

08:37.642 --> 08:39.561
do I see a chest hair?

08:39.561 --> 08:40.562
Look.

08:40.562 --> 08:42.564
[ Chuckles ]

08:42.564 --> 08:44.733
Yeah, we got to
show that thing off.

08:44.733 --> 08:46.693
Ray: Hey, Dylan.

08:46.693 --> 08:49.029
Have you heard about these
glowing worms in New Zealand

08:49.029 --> 08:51.740
that hang from caves and catch
their prey in slimy threads?

08:51.740 --> 08:53.450
Ray, please.

08:53.450 --> 08:54.784
I'm pretending
to do homework.

08:54.784 --> 08:55.785
[ Door opens ]

08:55.785 --> 08:57.287
Dad. Great news.

08:57.287 --> 08:58.538
I found my window
with Jillian.

08:58.538 --> 09:00.248
And I also found
the perfect short thing to say

09:00.248 --> 09:01.458
to show her I'm cool.

09:01.458 --> 09:03.168
Oh, no.
Ray, please, not the glow worms.

09:03.168 --> 09:04.377
Shh!

09:04.377 --> 09:05.920
Dad, have you heard
about these glowing worms

09:05.920 --> 09:07.172
in New Zealand that hang ‐‐
‐It's weak.

09:07.172 --> 09:08.256
‐It's tight!
‐Mnh‐mnh.

09:08.256 --> 09:10.050
[ Chair scrapes ]
Dad. Look.

09:14.095 --> 09:15.096
Huh?

09:15.096 --> 09:16.473
Look what I did.

09:16.473 --> 09:18.058
Come on.
Lousy neighbors.

09:18.058 --> 09:19.476
Tone set.

09:19.476 --> 09:20.977
Ohhh, Dylan,
you didn't.

09:20.977 --> 09:22.103
[ Sighs ]
What?

09:22.103 --> 09:23.354
It's the DiMeo way.

09:23.354 --> 09:25.732
No, this is not
who we are.

09:25.732 --> 09:27.025
Picking on people,
pulling pranks ‐‐

09:27.025 --> 09:28.151
that's a jerk move.

09:28.151 --> 09:30.695
The DiMeos are not jerks.

09:30.695 --> 09:31.863
We're idiots.

09:31.863 --> 09:33.907
What's the difference?

09:33.907 --> 09:35.408
People hate jerks.

09:35.408 --> 09:37.035
Jerks are mean.

09:37.035 --> 09:39.662
But idiots ‐‐
idiots are gonna mess up.

09:39.662 --> 09:41.664
And what are you gonna do ‐‐
get angry? They're idiots.

09:41.664 --> 09:45.627
So the world lets idiots
lead their idiot lives.

09:45.627 --> 09:47.545
<i>That's</i> what we want.

09:47.545 --> 09:49.380
Think he'll know
it came from us?

09:49.380 --> 09:50.840
Nah.

09:50.840 --> 09:52.092
He's probably
just pointing over here,

09:52.092 --> 09:53.718
saying,
"I'm a weirdo.

09:53.718 --> 09:55.804
I angrily point
at things I love."

09:55.804 --> 09:57.514
Young woman:
Everyone, this is JJ.

09:57.514 --> 09:59.349
All: Hi, JJ!

09:59.349 --> 10:01.518
JJ is interested in being
our new cheer manager,

10:01.518 --> 10:03.478
and I don't think the fact
that that's not a thing

10:03.478 --> 10:04.604
is any reason
to say "No."

10:04.604 --> 10:06.523
[ All cheering ]

10:06.523 --> 10:07.607
[ Giggles ]

10:07.607 --> 10:09.025
[ Giggles ]

10:09.025 --> 10:12.445
Oh, dude!
We got to go.

10:12.445 --> 10:14.197
You have
your appointment.

10:14.197 --> 10:18.409
"I always..."
M‐I ‐‐ "miss them.

10:18.409 --> 10:20.620
Yeah,
I don't know, man.

10:20.620 --> 10:24.040
"They need their manager."

10:26.876 --> 10:29.379
Are you trying to be adorable
right now?

10:29.379 --> 10:30.630
Fine.

10:30.630 --> 10:32.590
But if your mother calls,
we got to go.

10:32.590 --> 10:33.925
All right?

10:33.925 --> 10:38.096
All right. Let's see what
these young ladies got, huh?

10:38.096 --> 10:39.848
Can't be a guy who drives a van
and says that.

10:39.848 --> 10:41.057
I'll...be right over here.

10:41.057 --> 10:42.934
Joyce, I'm so sorry.

10:42.934 --> 10:45.311
JJ never misses
an appointment.

10:45.311 --> 10:48.189
I mean, he's got this new aide,
and, I mean, I just...

10:48.189 --> 10:50.233
I have to believe
that he's okay.

10:50.233 --> 10:51.651
You know what?
You're upset.

10:51.651 --> 10:53.945
I'll get out of your way.
Send me a check.

10:53.945 --> 10:56.531
A check? What check?
Why would I send you a check?

10:56.531 --> 10:59.033
For my time, of course.
And I drove here.

10:59.033 --> 11:01.327
Ahhhh.

11:01.327 --> 11:02.996
You're a pushy little hippie,
aren't you?

11:04.330 --> 11:05.623
Ray! Get in here!

11:07.709 --> 11:09.502
It's time
for your physical therapy.

11:09.502 --> 11:10.920
I'm...not JJ.

11:10.920 --> 11:12.297
I'm ‐‐
I'm the other one.

11:12.297 --> 11:14.674
I know who you are.
Your brother's MIA.

11:14.674 --> 11:16.676
If we pay for physical therapy,
we <i>get</i> physical therapy.

11:16.676 --> 11:18.261
Go on. Heal him.

11:18.261 --> 11:19.262
[ Cellphone clicks ]

11:19.262 --> 11:20.305
Now!

11:20.305 --> 11:22.307
Copy that.
All right. Follow me.

11:22.307 --> 11:23.308
All: Yeah!

11:23.308 --> 11:24.392
‐Whoo!
‐Whoo!

11:24.392 --> 11:26.394
[ Cellphone vibrates ]
Be aggressive!

11:26.394 --> 11:28.563
B‐E aggressive!
‐Whoo!

11:28.563 --> 11:31.399
[ Cheering continues
indistinctly ]

11:31.399 --> 11:35.069
♪♪

11:37.864 --> 11:39.407
Ready?

11:39.407 --> 11:41.326
Be aggressive!

11:41.326 --> 11:43.203
B‐E aggressive!

11:43.203 --> 11:44.037
Whoo!

11:45.914 --> 11:48.374
Looks like you're working up
a sweat, huh?

11:48.374 --> 11:51.461
Listen ‐‐
never a mistake.

11:51.461 --> 11:53.630
Mm‐hmm?

11:53.630 --> 11:55.381
Now, since this is
our first time working together,

11:55.381 --> 11:57.008
if you can't make it
all the way to the cone,

11:57.008 --> 11:58.718
no cause for shame.

11:58.718 --> 12:00.595
I think I'll manage.

12:03.640 --> 12:04.724
[ Chuckling ]
Oh, I'm sorry.

12:04.724 --> 12:06.476
What are you doing?

12:06.476 --> 12:08.186
Just walk
how you normally walk.

12:08.186 --> 12:09.520
This <i>is</i> how I walk.

12:11.147 --> 12:12.190
Oh, no. Okay.

12:12.190 --> 12:13.566
This is all wrong.

12:13.566 --> 12:15.360
Listen.
You pronate.

12:15.360 --> 12:17.695
You have a petite gait
with a 20‐degree kickout.

12:17.695 --> 12:20.031
It's gonna cause back pain
and organ imbalances.

12:20.031 --> 12:21.157
I mean,
it's fine for today,

12:21.157 --> 12:22.492
but is this
your long‐term walking plan?

12:22.492 --> 12:23.826
[ Whimpering ]
I mean, it <i>was!</i>

12:23.826 --> 12:26.162
Okay. Don't worry. Don't worry.
We'll get you there.

12:26.162 --> 12:28.665
It's gonna take work ‐‐
hard work ‐‐

12:28.665 --> 12:30.458
but we are gonna do it,
all right?

12:30.458 --> 12:32.168
Let's go back to the top, here.
We're gonna try again.

12:32.168 --> 12:33.962
But this time,
plant the heel,

12:33.962 --> 12:35.380
little toe mound,
big toe mound.

12:35.380 --> 12:37.090
Swing the opposite arm
as you plant

12:37.090 --> 12:38.132
with an imaginary string
pulling you up,

12:38.132 --> 12:39.384
elongating your form.

12:39.384 --> 12:40.510
Go.

12:41.844 --> 12:43.346
[ Exhales sharply ]

12:43.346 --> 12:45.139
♪♪

12:51.646 --> 12:53.064
[ Breathing heavily ]

12:53.064 --> 12:55.108
What have you done
to me?!

12:55.108 --> 12:58.194
All:
DiMeo! DiMeo! JJ DiMeo!

12:58.194 --> 13:01.447
DiMeo! DiMeo! JJ DiMeo!

13:01.447 --> 13:02.657
Oi!
Aah!
Aah!

13:02.657 --> 13:04.450
You're watching
cheerleaders?!

13:04.450 --> 13:05.702
I've been worried sick!

13:05.702 --> 13:08.871
2, 4, 6, 8,
who do we take for granted?

13:08.871 --> 13:10.957
Wouldn't you just say
"Not appreciate"?

13:10.957 --> 13:12.542
I've been calling you
for an hour.

13:12.542 --> 13:15.128
Oh, really?
Where's my phone?

13:15.128 --> 13:18.089
I'm sorry, but, um...
we were just having fun.

13:18.089 --> 13:19.215
And where are
your clothes?

13:19.215 --> 13:20.925
I gave him
a little upgrade.

13:20.925 --> 13:23.511
Ohh.
New and improved, is it?

13:23.511 --> 13:25.054
All it took was
a day away from <i>me.</i>

13:25.054 --> 13:26.097
Great.

13:27.265 --> 13:28.141
You know what?
Give me your keys.

13:31.602 --> 13:33.855
Come on, JJ ‐‐ if that is indeed
still your name.

13:35.565 --> 13:37.025
All: Kenneth! Kenneth!

13:37.025 --> 13:39.027
JJ and Kenneth!

13:39.027 --> 13:41.112
Kenneth! Kenneth! JJ...
Chant about the mom.

13:41.112 --> 13:42.655
... and Kenneth!
The mom!

13:42.655 --> 13:43.740
Kenneth!
JJ and Kenneth!
Mom, mom, the mom!

13:43.740 --> 13:44.490
JJ and Kenneth!
The mom!

13:47.869 --> 13:49.704
Stop making excuses for the man.
I don't want to hear it.

13:49.704 --> 13:50.788
Mom, we need to talk.

13:50.788 --> 13:52.415
I'm a petite walker
who pronates

13:52.415 --> 13:54.125
[ Door closes ]
with a 20‐degree
kickout.

13:54.125 --> 13:55.334
Everybody knows that, Ray.
It's not the time.

13:55.334 --> 13:57.128
I don't trust the man.

13:57.128 --> 13:59.380
He left you in the street.
He missed your appointment.

14:00.423 --> 14:02.341
Nope.
Don't drag me into this.

14:02.341 --> 14:03.134
I have walking videos
to watch.

14:06.679 --> 14:09.891
"He gives me stuff
you can't."

14:09.891 --> 14:11.726
What? Like fun?

14:11.726 --> 14:13.603
I'm very, very fun.
I'm a barrel of laughs.

14:13.603 --> 14:16.272
"You think you know
all I want."

14:16.272 --> 14:17.607
But I do!

14:17.607 --> 14:19.859
I literally
wrote the book, JJ.

14:19.859 --> 14:21.360
I know you
better than you know yourself.

14:21.360 --> 14:22.653
[ Scoffs ]

14:22.653 --> 14:24.906
‐I'm not saying that.
‐What?

14:27.533 --> 14:29.410
"I hate 'The Bachelor.'"

14:29.410 --> 14:30.870
[ Gasps ]
Take that back!

14:32.413 --> 14:34.040
[ Doorbell rings ]
What's the play?

14:34.040 --> 14:35.750
Don't worry.
Follow my lead.

14:35.750 --> 14:38.586
Tom.
Hey, neighbor.

14:38.586 --> 14:41.047
Don't, okay?
That word means something.

14:41.047 --> 14:43.132
This is about
not keeping the house up.

14:43.132 --> 14:44.425
Okay, listen.
I've thought about it.

14:44.425 --> 14:46.803
[ Trunk opens ]
It is really
not too much to ask.

14:46.803 --> 14:47.970
We ‐‐ we have...

14:47.970 --> 14:50.139
Oh! Again!

14:50.139 --> 14:52.225
Who keeps
sending us pizzas?

14:52.225 --> 14:53.726
Tom: Wait. What?

14:53.726 --> 14:55.019
I ‐‐ [ Sighs ]

14:55.019 --> 14:57.313
Jimmy,
I owe you an apology.

14:57.313 --> 14:58.981
Why?
Are ‐‐ Are <i>you</i> doing this?

14:58.981 --> 15:01.526
Tom!
We're neighbors!

15:01.526 --> 15:04.278
No. Someone's been
sending <i>me</i> pizzas, okay?

15:04.278 --> 15:05.029
I thought
<i>you</i> were pranking <i>me.</i>

15:05.029 --> 15:06.114
Well, if I was,

15:06.114 --> 15:08.157
then I'm also
pranking myself,

15:08.157 --> 15:10.743
so...it's not that.

15:10.743 --> 15:13.538
Oh! [ Snaps fingers ]
You know who I bet it is?

15:13.538 --> 15:15.665
It's this Charlie guy ‐‐
lives two streets over.

15:15.665 --> 15:16.666
Little guy? Shifty?

15:16.666 --> 15:18.000
No.
Yeah.
I've seen him.

15:19.794 --> 15:23.673
Okay. Not a great first day
for Kenneth.

15:23.673 --> 15:26.259
Yeah, but it makes for a
fantastic <i>last</i> one, doesn't it?

15:26.259 --> 15:28.302
Can you believe
that JJ thinks

15:28.302 --> 15:30.138
that man knows him better
than I do

15:30.138 --> 15:31.848
<i>and</i> that he's more fun?

15:31.848 --> 15:33.516
Wait a minute.
Is that what this is?

15:33.516 --> 15:35.601
If Kenneth doesn't have
what it takes,

15:35.601 --> 15:37.562
okay, he's got to go.

15:37.562 --> 15:40.106
But if this is about
you feeling threatened,

15:40.106 --> 15:41.691
you <i>have</i> to get over it.

15:41.691 --> 15:43.818
No, no, no. It's the first one.
It's the one you liked.

15:43.818 --> 15:44.777
Can I fire him now?

15:44.777 --> 15:45.987
[ Sighs ]

15:45.987 --> 15:48.114
Look, I mean it.

15:48.114 --> 15:50.408
Doesn't matter if he's fun.
It's not what the job's about.

15:50.408 --> 15:53.661
The job is about
JJ's dignity and safety.

15:53.661 --> 15:56.122
It's about feeding him
and showering him

15:56.122 --> 15:58.875
and taking care
of his basic needs.

15:58.875 --> 16:01.085
Kenneth does not have
what it takes.

16:01.085 --> 16:02.128
[ Sighs ]

16:02.128 --> 16:04.630
JJ loves Kenneth.

16:04.630 --> 16:05.882
This is gonna sting.

16:05.882 --> 16:07.592
[ Sighs ]

16:07.592 --> 16:09.135
You're right.

16:09.135 --> 16:10.720
I'll get the principal
to do it, eh?

16:10.720 --> 16:12.263
[ School bell rings ]

16:12.263 --> 16:13.764
Did she say
what this was about?

16:13.764 --> 16:14.891
She did not.

16:16.434 --> 16:18.728
Mrs. DiMeo.

16:18.728 --> 16:21.230
If this is about the stuff that
we took from the lost‐and‐found,

16:21.230 --> 16:22.440
tell her we'll return it.

16:22.440 --> 16:23.691
He just liked it.

16:23.691 --> 16:26.861
And finding Crocs in my size ‐‐
[ Chuckles ]

16:26.861 --> 16:28.029
I felt like
it was a sign.

16:28.029 --> 16:29.280
I'll be sure
to convey that.

16:30.907 --> 16:34.410
I know that <i>you</i> called
this meeting, but I‐I have news.

16:34.410 --> 16:37.496
It turns out there's training
Kenneth would require,

16:37.496 --> 16:40.666
and in a world where
there are qualified applicants,

16:40.666 --> 16:42.543
the district
can't justify the expense.

16:42.543 --> 16:44.712
The request was denied.

16:44.712 --> 16:46.088
[ Chuckles ]

16:47.048 --> 16:49.300
You seem...broken up.

16:49.300 --> 16:50.885
Perhaps
I should tell them myself?

16:50.885 --> 16:51.636
[ Inhales deeply ]

16:51.636 --> 16:54.388
Yeah. Do that.

16:54.388 --> 16:55.598
Where's my son?

16:55.598 --> 16:57.099
He had to use
the restroom.

16:57.099 --> 16:59.101
But he needs <i>me</i>
for that.

16:59.101 --> 17:01.145
Kenneth:
All right, pal.

17:01.145 --> 17:02.730
It's okay, buddy.
I got you.

17:02.730 --> 17:05.066
Nice and easy.

17:05.066 --> 17:07.026
All right.
All right, it's all good.

17:07.026 --> 17:08.402
You'd do the same for <i>me,</i>
right?

17:08.402 --> 17:10.029
Yeah.

17:10.029 --> 17:13.407
All right, but don't make me
guess next time, okay?

17:13.407 --> 17:15.910
If you hold it in too long,
then we got trouble.

17:15.910 --> 17:18.204
We already took the last
pair of pants in your size.

17:18.204 --> 17:19.789
[ JJ chuckles ]

17:19.789 --> 17:21.290
[ Chuckles ]

17:21.290 --> 17:24.961
Yeah, no need to thank me.
We're boys.

17:24.961 --> 17:26.420
We're keeping Kenneth.

17:26.420 --> 17:28.089
Is this the arguing thing
from before?

17:28.089 --> 17:29.674
Oh, goody!
What do I say now?

17:29.674 --> 17:31.008
No, no.
This isn't a conversation.

17:31.008 --> 17:32.426
But ‐‐ wait.
The list.

17:32.426 --> 17:34.136
Yeah, you know what everyone
on that list has in common?

17:34.136 --> 17:35.179
White men.

17:35.179 --> 17:36.764
Well,
h‐have you seen it?

17:36.764 --> 17:39.267
I‐I can't imagine
that Grace Huang is ‐‐

17:39.267 --> 17:40.393
It's very simple.

17:40.393 --> 17:42.853
Terminate a child's aide
based on race

17:42.853 --> 17:44.355
and have
a giant PR nightmare

17:44.355 --> 17:45.648
or make this work.

17:45.648 --> 17:46.607
Understood?

17:46.607 --> 17:48.276
[ Sighs ]
I can do it.

17:48.276 --> 17:50.027
I have dirt
on the superintendent.

17:50.027 --> 17:51.362
He's my brother,
but screw it.

17:51.362 --> 17:52.154
[ Dialing ]

17:53.531 --> 17:55.741
Oh. Hey, Ray.

17:55.741 --> 17:57.118
Hi, Jillian.

17:57.118 --> 17:58.786
I saw something online,
and I thought of you.

17:58.786 --> 18:00.871
Have you heard about these
glowing worms in New Zealand

18:00.871 --> 18:03.249
that hang from caves and catch
their prey in slimy threads?

18:03.249 --> 18:04.417
I saw a video.

18:04.417 --> 18:07.253
When they glow,
it looks like the night sky.

18:07.253 --> 18:08.588
Right! That's what made me
think of you ‐‐

18:08.588 --> 18:10.047
because
we both love astronomy.

18:10.047 --> 18:12.216
[ Chuckles ]
That's sweet.

18:12.216 --> 18:13.884
[ School bell rings ]

18:13.884 --> 18:15.428
Time for class.
Walk with me.

18:15.428 --> 18:17.430
Joyce: [ Echoing ]
<i>Walk to the cone.</i>

18:17.430 --> 18:19.223
<i>Petite walker.</i>

18:19.223 --> 18:21.350
<i>Walk how you normally walk.</i>

18:21.350 --> 18:23.311
<i>You stupid petite walker!</i>

18:23.311 --> 18:24.687
<i>You're a disgrace!</i>

18:24.687 --> 18:26.355
<i>You'll never amount</i>
<i>to anything!</i>

18:26.355 --> 18:28.107
She didn't even say that.

18:28.107 --> 18:30.693
♪♪

18:30.693 --> 18:32.320
Are you all right?

18:32.320 --> 18:33.446
[ Scoffs ]

18:33.446 --> 18:34.905
Just go!

18:36.616 --> 18:39.285
Why did you
have to make me walk?!

18:39.285 --> 18:41.329
So, all the principal
wanted to know

18:41.329 --> 18:42.663
was whether we were happy
with Kenneth.

18:42.663 --> 18:44.081
And are we?

18:44.081 --> 18:45.291
We are.

18:45.291 --> 18:46.667
I mean,
it's an adjustment ‐‐

18:46.667 --> 18:49.086
to you
and a little to my son.

18:49.086 --> 18:51.380
But I'll try.

18:51.380 --> 18:54.091
To be frank, yesterday,
I didn't trust or like you.

18:54.091 --> 18:55.509
Now I trust you.

18:55.509 --> 18:57.053
It's a start.

18:57.053 --> 18:58.929
Dad.
Check it out.

18:58.929 --> 19:00.181
[ Indistinct shouting ]

19:00.181 --> 19:01.557
I bet that's Charlie.

19:01.557 --> 19:03.768
Wow. Tom's really
letting him have it.

19:03.768 --> 19:05.353
Poor guy.
Collateral damage.

19:05.353 --> 19:06.729
Wait. So we're just gonna
let this happen?

19:08.147 --> 19:09.982
Seems like
kind of a jerk move.

19:09.982 --> 19:13.069
I didn't want any pizza
that night, Charlie, okay?

19:13.069 --> 19:15.446
I'd already eaten.
I didn't do it!

19:15.446 --> 19:16.822
Now, now, now, now.
Now, wait. Hang on.

19:16.822 --> 19:19.033
It wasn't Charlie.

19:19.033 --> 19:20.826
It was us.

19:20.826 --> 19:22.078
You?

19:22.078 --> 19:23.329
We did it.
I'm sorry.

19:23.329 --> 19:24.789
It was just
a messed‐up try

19:24.789 --> 19:27.249
to announce ourselves
to the neighborhood.

19:27.249 --> 19:30.169
You're a nice guy,
and you ‐‐

19:30.169 --> 19:33.506
all of you ‐‐
deserve to know now,

19:33.506 --> 19:35.758
[ Chuckling ]
we're lousy neighbors.
Yeah.

19:35.758 --> 19:38.427
We're not gonna
take in our trash bins.

19:38.427 --> 19:40.638
We're not gonna
fix up our house.

19:40.638 --> 19:42.973
If we receive
your packages,

19:42.973 --> 19:45.017
they will become
<i>our</i> packages.

19:45.017 --> 19:46.644
We had a snake
when we moved in.

19:46.644 --> 19:48.604
Where it is now
is anyone's guess.

19:48.604 --> 19:51.315
And we're definitely gonna swim
in all of your pools.

19:51.315 --> 19:52.400
We already did.

19:52.400 --> 19:55.444
It's just...
who we are.

19:55.444 --> 19:58.030
Let me
get this straight.

19:58.030 --> 20:00.574
You pranked us,
lied about it.

20:00.574 --> 20:02.993
You people are awful,
and you know it.

20:02.993 --> 20:04.495
And you've decided

20:04.495 --> 20:06.455
you're not gonna do
anything about it ever.

20:06.455 --> 20:07.581
I mean,
you people are jerks.

20:07.581 --> 20:08.374
Dylan: No.

20:09.583 --> 20:11.210
We're idiots.

20:11.210 --> 20:12.920
♪♪

20:17.341 --> 20:19.635
I just work here.

20:19.635 --> 20:20.886
[ Chuckles ]

20:24.682 --> 20:27.351
Lauren B.: [ <i>Gasps</i> ]
<i>Oh, my God.</i>

20:27.351 --> 20:30.855
[ <i>Romantic music plays</i> ]

20:30.855 --> 20:32.773
[ <i>Crowd cheering</i> ]

20:41.073 --> 20:43.033
[ Remote clicks ]
<i>Yes.</i>

20:43.033 --> 20:45.453
<i>Give me that thing.</i>
[ <i>Chuckles</i> ]

20:45.453 --> 20:48.748
♪♪

20:48.748 --> 20:50.875
You too, darling.

20:50.875 --> 20:52.877
You'll always be my baby.

20:55.212 --> 20:57.006
[ Grunts ]
